    <briefdescription>
<para>The <ref refid="a01273" kindref="compound">IterationBased</ref> strategy for adaptive step sizing. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This strategy adjusts the step size based on the ratio of target iterations to previous iterations.</para>
<para>The step size is changed according to the number of iterations of the previous step <formula id="0">\[ \hat{s}_{k+1} = \sqrt{\frac{\hat{i}}{i_k}}\hat{s}_k,  \]</formula> where <formula id="1">$\hat{s}_{k+1} $</formula> is the new stesize and <formula id="2">$\hat{i}$</formula> is the desired number of iterations and <formula id="3">$i_k$</formula> is the number of iterations of the previous step. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
